JOHANNESBURG – Godfrey Lebeya has been appointed as the new head of the Hawks, Cabinet confirmed on Thursday. He comes with an impressive record - being a career policeman, a former deputy police commissioner, an advocate and having completed his doctorate on organised crime. Communications Minister Nomvula Mokonyane made the announcement during a post-Cabinet briefing. Lebeya replaces Yolisa Matakata, who was appointed acting Hawks head by former police minister Fikile Mbalula. READ: Ntlemeza appeal dismissed This after Berning Ntlemeza’s appointment to the role was ruled irregular and unlawful by a court. eNCA